`input.next()` returns a `String`. Always.

To fix this, specify the Scanner method the instance should use:

```
public class UserInput&lt;T&gt; {
    private Function&lt;Scanner, T&gt; reader;
    
    public UserInput(Function&lt;Scanner, T&gt; reader) {
        this.reader = reader;
    }
    
    public List&lt;T&gt; getUserInput(Integer number_inputs) {
        List&lt;T&gt; inputs = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
        for (int i=1; i &lt; number_inputs+1; i++) {
            System.out.println(&quot;Enter number &quot; + i);
            T userInput = reader.apply(input);
            inputs.add(userInput);
        }
        return inputs;
    }
}
```

